<subSubSection id="11BB6561DF37FFAF8BF5FC1BB85CF556" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="591E36EADF37FFAF8BF5FC1BB85CF556" blockId="12.[151,1436,825,2004]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="6BD5EAF8DF37FFAF8BF5FC1BBB37F29D" bold="true" box="[199,321,969,994]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is immediately distinguishable by paired submedial longitudinal stripes on presutural area of scutum and extensive patch of golden pile on abdominal tergites 
<number id="EF6924CDDF37FFAF88F9FC3FB98EF57A" box="[971,1016,1005,1029]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5</number>
. Wing brownish infuscated, with diffuse pale transverse band in middle.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="11BB6561DF37FFAF8BF5FBE7BBCAF6CF" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="description">
<paragraph id="591E36EADF37FFAF8BF5FBE7BE72F45A" blockId="12.[151,1436,825,2004]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="6BD5EAF8DF37FFAF8BF5FBE7BB2FF531" bold="true" box="[199,345,1077,1102]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Description.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="21B6767ADF37FFAF8A6CFBE7BBEEF532" box="[350,408,1077,1101]" name="Malta" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Male</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="C19A2A6FDF37FFAF8A95FBE7B872F532" box="[423,516,1077,1101]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 56" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1673,1696]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1652]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[151,1436,193,1652]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 56. Ptilocera spp. P. continua, pretarsus of female fore leg in ventral view (51). P. aureopilosa, female abdomen in dorsal view (52). P. paradisea, distal half of male abdomen in dorsal view (53). P. continua, female abdomen in lateral view (54). P. quadridentata, dorsal part of male terminalia in ventral view (55) and genital capsule and aedeagal complex in dorsal view (56)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278491/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Figs. 
<number id="EF6924CDDF37FFAF8AD4FBE7B872F532" box="[486,516,1077,1101]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="53.65">53</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<number id="EF6924CDDF37FFAF8922FBE7B8E9F532" box="[528,671,1077,1101]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="89.555" valueMax="114.0" valueMin="65.11">
<figureCitation id="C19A2A6FDF37FFAF8922FBE7B858F532" box="[528,558,1077,1101]" captionStart="FIGURES 65 – 73" captionStartId="33.[151,264,1756,1779]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1732]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[151,1436,193,1735]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURES 65 – 73. Ptilocera spp., wings: P. p a r a d i s e a, male holotype (65), P. quadridentata, male (66) and female (67), P. s i m - plex sp. nov., male holotype (68) and female (69), P. smaragdina, male (70) and female (71), P. violacea, male (72) and female (73)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278493/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">65</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="C19A2A6FDF37FFAF890BFBE7B8E9F532" box="[569,671,1077,1101]" captionStart="FIGURES 108 – 114" captionStartId="39.[151,264,1756,1779]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,193,1716]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[151,1436,193,1735]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 108 – 114. Ptilocera spp. 108 – 109. P. kerteszi sp. nov., female holotype, dorsal view (108), antenna (109). 110 – 114. P. paradisea, male holotype, dorsal view (110), antenna (111), genital capsule (112), aedeagal complex (113), proctiger, cerci and epandrium (114)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278498/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">110–114</figureCitation>
</number>
). Length (mm): body 9.0; wing 7.7 (only 
<typeStatus id="861A8848DF37FFAF8F5FFBE7BEB9F532" box="[1133,1231,1077,1101]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">holotype</typeStatus>
examined). Head. Upper frons with erect, very short hairs in front of anterior ocellus. Antenna as in 
<figureCitation id="C19A2A6FDF37FFAF8F04FB8BBEE2F50E" box="[1078,1172,1113,1137]" captionStart="FIGURES 108 – 114" captionStartId="39.[151,264,1756,1779]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,193,1716]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[151,1436,193,1735]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 108 – 114. Ptilocera spp. 108 – 109. P. kerteszi sp. nov., female holotype, dorsal view (108), antenna (109). 110 – 114. P. paradisea, male holotype, dorsal view (110), antenna (111), genital capsule (112), aedeagal complex (113), proctiger, cerci and epandrium (114)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278498/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Fig. 
<number id="EF6924CDDF37FFAF8F58FB8BBEE2F50E" box="[1130,1172,1113,1137]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="111.0">111</number>
</figureCitation>
, antennal scape brown, pedicel light brown, flagellomeres uniformly dark brown. First two flagellomeres short and densely haired, with sensory pits, basal flagellomere almost twice as long as broad, apical flagellomere 3.5 times as long as preceding flagellomere. Lower frons bare, shining dark brown, with two small triangular silverish tomentose spots. Face covered with erect silverish white pile. Proboscis brown, with whitish hairs. Palpus brown, two-segmented. Postocular area not distinct in upper part and very narrow in lower part of head in profile.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="591E36EADF37FFAF8BF5FAE3B92FF737" blockId="12.[151,1436,825,2004]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Thorax (
<figureCitation id="C19A2A6FDF37FFAF8A1AFAE3BBF1F436" box="[296,391,1329,1353]" captionStart="FIGURES 108 – 114" captionStartId="39.[151,264,1756,1779]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,193,1716]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[151,1436,193,1735]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 108 – 114. Ptilocera spp. 108 – 109. P. kerteszi sp. nov., female holotype, dorsal view (108), antenna (109). 110 – 114. P. paradisea, male holotype, dorsal view (110), antenna (111), genital capsule (112), aedeagal complex (113), proctiger, cerci and epandrium (114)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278498/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Fig. 
<number id="EF6924CDDF37FFAF8A6FFAE3BBF1F436" box="[349,391,1329,1353]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="110.0">110</number>
</figureCitation>
) black, densely punctate, with shining golden scattered scales and with two shining, narrow, longitudinal, emerald stripes ending at transverse suture. Postpronotal callus brown, with erect brownish hairs at base; postalar callus blackish, prealar prominence rounded. Scutellum flattened, with slender, yellowish brown spines. Medial spines distinctly longer than half length of scutellum at middle. Anepisternum densely punctate, with very short and appressed brown pile. Wing pattern as in 
<figureCitation id="C19A2A6FDF37FFAF8866FA13B9DEF4A6" box="[852,936,1473,1497]" captionStart="FIGURES 65 – 73" captionStartId="33.[151,264,1756,1779]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1732]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[151,1436,193,1735]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURES 65 – 73. Ptilocera spp., wings: P. p a r a d i s e a, male holotype (65), P. quadridentata, male (66) and female (67), P. s i m - plex sp. nov., male holotype (68) and female (69), P. smaragdina, male (70) and female (71), P. violacea, male (72) and female (73)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278493/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Fig. 
<number id="EF6924CDDF37FFAF88BBFA13B9DEF4A6" box="[905,936,1473,1497]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="65.0">65</number>
</figureCitation>
. Wing membrane brownish infuscated, with pale (rather hyaline than yellowish) transverse band from crossvein R-M, through distal half of discal cell to basal part of cell m 
<number id="EF6924CDDF37FFAF8A00F9CABB4CF759" box="[306,314,1560,1574]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="2.0">2</number>
. Calypter brown, densely brownish haired along margin. Halter with brown stalk and black knob. Legs: coxa, femur and tibia dark brown, tarsi yellowish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="591E36EADF37FFAF8BF5F986B8DDF617" blockId="12.[151,1436,825,2004]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Abdomen (
<figureCitation id="C19A2A6FDF37FFAF8A7AF986BBD5F713" box="[328,419,1620,1644]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 56" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1673,1696]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1652]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[151,1436,193,1652]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 56. Ptilocera spp. P. continua, pretarsus of female fore leg in ventral view (51). P. aureopilosa, female abdomen in dorsal view (52). P. paradisea, distal half of male abdomen in dorsal view (53). P. continua, female abdomen in lateral view (54). P. quadridentata, dorsal part of male terminalia in ventral view (55) and genital capsule and aedeagal complex in dorsal view (56)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278491/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Figs 
<number id="EF6924CDDF37FFAF8AB7F986BBD5F713" box="[389,419,1620,1644]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="53.11">53</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="C19A2A6FDF37FFAF8A81F986BBABF713" box="[435,477,1620,1644]" captionStart="FIGURES 108 – 114" captionStartId="39.[151,264,1756,1779]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,193,1716]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[151,1436,193,1735]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 108 – 114. Ptilocera spp. 108 – 109. P. kerteszi sp. nov., female holotype, dorsal view (108), antenna (109). 110 – 114. P. paradisea, male holotype, dorsal view (110), antenna (111), genital capsule (112), aedeagal complex (113), proctiger, cerci and epandrium (114)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278498/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">110</figureCitation>
) black to dark brown, without obvious reflections, finely punctate, with very fine micropile. Tergite 
<number id="EF6924CDDF37FFAF8A57F9AABB05F7EF" box="[357,371,1656,1680]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1.0">1</number>
and 
<number id="EF6924CDDF37FFAF8A9AF9AABBC0F7EF" box="[424,438,1656,1680]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="2.0">2</number>
with brown pile along lateral margins, tergite 
<number id="EF6924CDDF37FFAF888AF9AAB9B0F7EF" box="[952,966,1656,1680]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="3.0">3</number>
with paired lateral hair patches consisting of golden pile, similar but dense pilosity extensively covering tergite 
<number id="EF6924CDDF37FFAF8880F94EB9B6F7CB" box="[946,960,1692,1716]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="4.0">4</number>
and almost completely covering tergite 
<number id="EF6924CDDF37FFAF8EBCF94EBFEAF7CB" box="[1422,1436,1692,1716]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="5.0">5</number>
(
<figureCitation id="C19A2A6FDF37FFAF8BADF912BB76F7A7" box="[159,256,1728,1752]" captionStart="FIGURES 108 – 114" captionStartId="39.[151,264,1756,1779]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,193,1716]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[151,1436,193,1735]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 108 – 114. Ptilocera spp. 108 – 109. P. kerteszi sp. nov., female holotype, dorsal view (108), antenna (109). 110 – 114. P. paradisea, male holotype, dorsal view (110), antenna (111), genital capsule (112), aedeagal complex (113), proctiger, cerci and epandrium (114)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278498/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Fig. 
<number id="EF6924CDDF37FFAF8BE1F912BB76F7A7" box="[211,256,1728,1752]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="110.0">110</number>
</figureCitation>
). Sternites brown, mainly bare. 
<collectingCountry id="21B6767ADF37FFAF8953F912B8EDF7A7" box="[609,667,1728,1752]" name="Malta" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Male</collectingCountry>
terminalia (
<figureCitation id="C19A2A6FDF37FFAF8813F912B9C9F7A7" box="[801,959,1728,1752]" captionStart="FIGURES 108 – 114" captionStartId="39.[151,264,1756,1779]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,193,1716]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[151,1436,193,1735]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 108 – 114. Ptilocera spp. 108 – 109. P. kerteszi sp. nov., female holotype, dorsal view (108), antenna (109). 110 – 114. P. paradisea, male holotype, dorsal view (110), antenna (111), genital capsule (112), aedeagal complex (113), proctiger, cerci and epandrium (114)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278498/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Figs 
<number id="EF6924CDDF37FFAF886BF912B9C9F7A7" box="[857,959,1728,1752]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="113.0" valueMax="114.0" valueMin="112.0">112–114</number>
</figureCitation>
): Proctiger (
<figureCitation id="C19A2A6FDF37FFAF8F7FF912BEDCF7A7" box="[1101,1194,1728,1752]" captionStart="FIGURES 108 – 114" captionStartId="39.[151,264,1756,1779]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,193,1716]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[151,1436,193,1735]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 108 – 114. Ptilocera spp. 108 – 109. P. kerteszi sp. nov., female holotype, dorsal view (108), antenna (109). 110 – 114. P. paradisea, male holotype, dorsal view (110), antenna (111), genital capsule (112), aedeagal complex (113), proctiger, cerci and epandrium (114)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278498/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Fig. 
<number id="EF6924CDDF37FFAF8FB2F912BEDCF7A7" box="[1152,1194,1728,1752]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="114.0">114</number>
</figureCitation>
) unusually high, subtriangular, cerci not reaching beyond tip of proctiger. Genital capsule (
<figureCitation id="C19A2A6FDF37FFAF889EF936BE7CF783" box="[940,1034,1764,1788]" captionStart="FIGURES 108 – 114" captionStartId="39.[151,264,1756,1779]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,193,1716]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[151,1436,193,1735]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 108 – 114. Ptilocera spp. 108 – 109. P. kerteszi sp. nov., female holotype, dorsal view (108), antenna (109). 110 – 114. P. paradisea, male holotype, dorsal view (110), antenna (111), genital capsule (112), aedeagal complex (113), proctiger, cerci and epandrium (114)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278498/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Fig. 
<number id="EF6924CDDF37FFAF88D2F936BE7CF783" box="[992,1034,1764,1788]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="112.0">112</number>
</figureCitation>
) subquadrate, posterior medial process of genital capsule bilobed, resembling that of 
<taxonomicName id="9EA14D69DF37FFAF89EAF8DBB920F65F" box="[728,854,1801,1824]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Ptilocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="continua">
<emphasis id="6BD5EAF8DF37FFAF89EAF8DBB920F65F" box="[728,854,1801,1824]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. continua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but middle incision more pointed, gonostylus leafshaped as in other species. Posterolateral papillae of aedeagal complex relatively long, with two transverse ridges but without any basal hyaline spines (
<figureCitation id="C19A2A6FDF37FFAF890FF882B8E8F617" box="[573,670,1872,1896]" captionStart="FIGURES 108 – 114" captionStartId="39.[151,264,1756,1779]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,193,1716]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[151,1436,193,1735]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 108 – 114. Ptilocera spp. 108 – 109. P. kerteszi sp. nov., female holotype, dorsal view (108), antenna (109). 110 – 114. P. paradisea, male holotype, dorsal view (110), antenna (111), genital capsule (112), aedeagal complex (113), proctiger, cerci and epandrium (114)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278498/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Fig. 
<number id="EF6924CDDF37FFAF8943F882B8E8F617" box="[625,670,1872,1896]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="113.0">113</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="591E36EADF37FFAF8BF5F8A6BBEBF6F3" blockId="12.[151,1436,825,2004]" box="[199,413,1908,1932]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Female. Unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="591E36EADF37FFAF8BF5F845BBCAF6CF" blockId="12.[151,1436,825,2004]" box="[199,444,1943,1968]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="6BD5EAF8DF37FFAF8BF5F845BB4DF6CF" bold="true" box="[199,315,1943,1968]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Variation.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
